<subSubSection id="49C942EEFFF3392BEBD2C588FBEA5866" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="016C1165FFF3392BEBD2C588FEAA59E3" blockId="93.[227,341,699,725]" box="[227,341,699,725]" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">
<heading id="5A24A609FFF3392BEBD2C588FEAA59E3" bold="true" box="[227,341,699,725]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" reason="3">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFF3392BEBD2C588FEAA59E3" bold="true" box="[227,341,699,725]" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="016C1165FFF3392BEBD2C5DFFBEA5866" blockId="93.[226,1437,747,848]" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Two specimens are characterized by a long cauda, whose ventrally bent portion does not exceed 90 degrees, a rather short ostium, and a pointed rostrum. They apparently represent an undescribed species. However, their preservation does not allow a precise characterization.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
